texts.text: >The fight with Alice goes on as the Liberators race through the maze...
C'mon Alice! Catch me if you can!
Found you! Take that!
Now, Seiran!
On it! You're back's wide open, missy!
>Seiran's attack connects... with the wall that suddenly appeared behind Alice!
Dammit... Guess it's not going to be that easy...
Ahahaha, and now I've found you too! That was very sneaky of you to come from behind!
And... I found two more! Right over there!
Oof!
Goddamn! That was close!
Shionyan! Ririn! You okay?!
I'm fine! I anticipated this! Everything's according to plan.
Your turn, Mr. Meat!
...? What is this? A bauble?
*Shriek*
>The round object that rolled to Alice's feet explodes, emitting a thick smoke!
Special smoke grenade. Doesn't do much damage, but that's not the point..
Now we can surprise her because she can't see.
Let her have it Newbie!
Gotcha!
Come on!

Huh?
*Shriek*
>Under the cover provided by the smoke,
>[sys user_name] unleashes an attack at full power that hits Alice!
Did we get her?!
No... Not completely. But I think we've weakened her a lot.

*Sniff*
*Sob*
Why? Why are you all being so mean to me...?
>Alice squats down crying...

H-Hey guys...
Do we really have to kill her?
I mean... Killing a crying little girl is kinda...
I understand the sentiment, but it has to be done.
She's the one trying to kill us just a moment ago, remember?
She may look like a harmless little girl, but she's a demon that murdered a lot of people.
You have to look past her outward appearance and see her true nature.
Yeah... I know that, but...
...!! Get out of the way Ririn!
Huh?
>The ceiling above shifts into a spear-like shape and attacks Ririn!
Ugh... Ack...
Huh? I... I was about to get skewered...
Why did Alice go down instead of me?
Newbie, did you...
You killed her... To save me...
Somebody had to do it.
Are you hurt?
Yes, but...
I'm sorry... for putting you through that.
I-I'm okay! Thanks to you... I owe you my life...
...And I'm sorry, for putting you through that...
>Down on the ground, Alice begins to dissipate...

*Sob*
I don't want to... be alone...

A friend...
To be with me...
Alice...
I know it's a hard pill to swallow, but it can't be helped.
No matter how much she yearns for friends, she's just too much to handle for us humans.
...I see this is as far as it goes..
Wha-, another demon?!
Pardon me, but I'm here to take this girl's soul.
>The demon tips the urn in his hand, and Alice is sucked into it.
>Disappearing without a trace.
Ahh, she went in. That is well.
She is in a very weak state, but not unsalvageable.
Dammit! How many of them are there?! C'mon guys, get ready to fight!
You can be at ease, for I wish you no harm.
What? Then what...
Ah, I have yet to introduce myself. My name is Nebiros.
I am a necromancer, and gathering souls for my soul collection is a pet hobby of mine...
I just happened to be in the vicinity when I sensed a fascinating soul of much power,
so I came here to claim it for my collection.
So please, don't mind me.
...What a pervert.
I don't expect humans to understand the intricacies of soul collecting,
so you can think of me as you like.
Soul collecting? What have you done to Alice?!
You sucked her into that urn...
This is the Urn of Apprehension.
It can capture and seal within it any soul, be it human or demon.
Seal within... So you imprisoned her soul?
Correct. I know not why, but I have taken a great interest in this particular soul.
Don't worry, I will take good care of her.
>Nebiros gives the urn a fond pat.
But alas...
I was actually hoping you would be the ones to fall in battle, so that I may add your souls to my collection.
Your victory was most unexpected.
What? OUR souls?!
But... Very well, some other time maybe.
Don't count on it...
Ah, one more thing. I suggest that you make haste to escape this maze.
The soul of Alice is now sealed within the Urn of Apprehension,
which means this world is now an empty house without a master that will collapse unto itself shortly.
...Ah, speak of the devil.
We still got a lot to ask you, but I guess we don't have the time.
Be patient.
We shall meet again. Some time. Somewhere.
I hope not.
See ya.
Hmm, so cold and distant.
Shouldn't you say something like "see you again" in anticipation of future encounters?
Hmm, a human who looks forward to meeting a demon again, what a peculiar person.
My interest in you continues to grow.
*Chuckle*
>With that, the Liberators turn around and run off...
>A few days later...
>The News report is running on TV at the Hideout.
...An abandoned subway facility has caused a cave-in in Tokyo.
This subway facility was constructed 8 years ago as part of the Tokyo subway expansion plan,
which was shut down due to a myriad of mysterious accidents.
The facility then became a restricted zone,
and experts are now looking into how it caused the cave-in.
So that place was originally a subway facility under Tokyo...
Yes. I did some further digging myself,
and found the reason why there were so many accidents during its construction.
The construction disrupted a branch of the Dragon Stream that ran underground you see, making it change course.
I think that's why the facility was so affected by the Dragon Stream.
There's no way to know for sure,
but that place might have been infested with demons even before Alice wandered in there.
...One thing's for sure though. We need to get stronger.
So many innocent people died this time,
all because they had the bad luck of bein' summoned to that maze.
What if more powerful demons like Belial decide to visit our world?
Not everyone can summon demons to protect themselves,
so we who have the ability hafta get stronger.
Megakin's right.
I always thought that the "save the world" thing only happens in light novels and stuff.
To tell the truth, I didn't even really want to be a Dx2 at first.
But if powerful demons like that do make their way into our world,
then we're the only ones that can actually do something about it...
I don't presume we'll be able to protect the entire world from demons because it's too big a place,
but I'd like to protect my friends and my family. The people I care about the most.
That's all you need to do.
We can only protect those around us. Realistically, that's all you can ever hope to do.
So let us gain the strength to at least be able to accomplish this one thing without flaw.
That's all you need to do...
Wow, Meat Balloon is saying something cool for once. It's probably gonna rain tomorrow.
Ririn, I swear-
Okay okay, my bad! You're perfectly right. We gotta hustle from now on!
